  "target_summary": {
    "type": "continuous_regression",
    "utility_notes": [
      "preserve continuous online-news share regression signal without using target shares in theta",
      "target shares are highly right-tailed; median is about 1400 while the train maximum reaches 843300",
      "keyword popularity summaries such as kw_avg_avg and kw_max_avg are the strongest utility-side feature candidates",
      "self-reference share columns, topic/channel features, link/image counts, and sentiment/title fields provide additional regression signal",
      "utility evaluation in the existing pareto report uses regression RMSE with a log-clipped target transform; describe utility qualitatively rather than claim new experiment results",
      "target shares must never appear in theta even though it is the regression label"
    ]
  },
