  "risks": {
    "shape": [
      "keyword popularity and self-reference share columns are heavy-tailed and can be flattened by synthetic generation",
      "share-like feature columns such as self_reference_* can reach 843300 and have large zero masses",
      "media/link count columns are zero-inflated and right-tailed; num_videos is mostly zero but has rare large values",
      "kw_min_min, kw_avg_min, and kw_min_avg can contain sentinel-like -1 values; clipping them to nonnegative values distorts shape",
      "LDA_00 through LDA_04 are bounded topic proportions and should approximately preserve their simplex-like structure",
      "title subjectivity and sentiment columns have large exact-zero masses that should not be smoothed away"
    ],
    "trend": [
      "keyword min/max/avg groups should remain internally coherent rather than sampled independently",
      "self_reference_min_shares, self_reference_max_shares, and self_reference_avg_sharess form a dependent prior-popularity group",
      "n_unique_tokens, n_non_stop_words, and n_non_stop_unique_tokens share zero-content behavior and strong coupling",
      "LDA topic columns should retain topic-mixture constraints and channel/topic relationships",
      "positive and negative sentiment/rate columns are bounded and mutually constrained",
      "content length should remain plausible with link, self-link, image, video, and keyword counts"
    ],
    "privacy": [
      "configured privacy columns are timedelta, n_tokens_title, n_tokens_content, n_unique_tokens, and n_non_stop_words",
      "there is no direct human PII, but exact article profiles can create nearest-neighbor disclosure risk",
      "article age, content/title lengths, link/media counts, keyword popularity, self-reference shares, topic mix, channel, and weekday can form narrow fingerprints",
      "self-reference and keyword popularity columns have high-resolution values that can act as quasi-identifiers",
      "for 47 feature columns, current theta validation requires broad col_ps coverage of 24-40 columns; do not use a tiny privacy scope",
      "col_ps must remain below all feature columns and must never include the target shares"
    ],
    "utility": [
      "using only data_channel or weekday as col_u is too weak for regression utility",
      "dropping keyword popularity columns, especially kw_avg_avg and kw_max_avg, weakens share prediction utility",
      "self-reference share columns carry useful popularity signal and should remain available despite privacy risk",
      "LDA_02 has negative association with popularity while LDA_03 and some channel/weekend patterns add utility; topic/channel structure should not be washed out",
      "the target shares column must never appear in theta even though it is the regression label",
      "do not convert this local regression task into the source paper's historical 1400-share binary classification setup"
    ]
  },
